moves.name: Brave Bird
moves.desc: If the target lost HP, the user takes recoil damage equal to 33% the HP lost by the target, rounded half up, but not less than 1 HP.
moves.shortDesc: Has 33% recoil.

moves.name: Tailwind
moves.desc: For 4 turns, the user and its party members have their Speed doubled. Fails if this move is already in effect for the user's side.
moves.shortDesc: For 4 turns, allies' Speed is doubled.

moves.name: Roost
moves.desc: The user restores 1/2 of its maximum HP, rounded half up. If the user is not Terastallized, until the end of the turn Flying-type users lose their Flying type and pure Flying-type users become Normal type. Does nothing if the user's HP is full.
moves.shortDesc: Heals 50% HP. Flying-type removed 'til turn ends.

moves.name: Iron Head
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to make the target flinch.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to make the target flinch.

moves.name: Bulk Up
moves.desc: Raises the user's Attack and Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the user's Attack and Defense by 1.

moves.name: Protect
moves.desc: The user is protected from most attacks made by other Pokemon during this turn. This move has a 1/X chance of being successful, where X starts at 1 and triples each time this move is successfully used. X resets to 1 if this move fails, if the user's last move used is not Baneful Bunker, Burning Bulwark, Detect, Endure, King's Shield, Max Guard, Obstruct, Protect, Quick Guard, Silk Trap, Spiky Shield, or Wide Guard, or if it was one of those moves and the user's protection was broken. Fails if the user moves last this turn.
moves.shortDesc: Prevents moves from affecting the user this turn.

moves.name: Body Press
moves.desc: Damage is calculated using the user's Defense stat as its Attack, including stat stage changes. Other effects that modify the Attack stat are used as normal.
moves.shortDesc: Uses user's Def stat as Atk in damage calculation.

moves.name: Iron Defense
moves.desc: Raises the user's Defense by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the user's Defense by 2.

moves.name: Heavy Slam
moves.desc: The power of this move depends on (user's weight / target's weight), rounded down. Power is equal to 120 if the result is 5 or more, 100 if 4, 80 if 3, 60 if 2, and 40 if 1 or less. Damage doubles and no accuracy check is done if the target has used Minimize while active.
moves.shortDesc: More power the heavier the user than the target.

moves.name: Taunt
moves.desc: Prevents the target from using non-damaging moves for its next three turns. Pokemon with the Oblivious Ability or protected by the Aroma Veil Ability are immune.
moves.shortDesc: Target can't use status moves its next 3 turns.

moves.name: U-turn
moves.desc: If this move is successful and the user has not fainted, the user switches out even if it is trapped and is replaced immediately by a selected party member. The user does not switch out if there are no unfainted party members, or if the target switched out using an Eject Button or through the effect of the Emergency Exit or Wimp Out Abilities.
moves.shortDesc: User switches out after damaging the target.

moves.name: Tera Blast
moves.desc: If the user is Terastallized, this move becomes a physical attack if the user's Attack is greater than its Special Attack, including stat stage changes, and this move's type becomes the same as the user's Tera Type. In addition, if the user's Tera Type is Stellar, this move has 100 power, is super effective against Terastallized targets and neutral against other targets, and lowers the user's Attack and Special Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: If Terastallized: Phys. if Atk > SpA, type = Tera.

moves.name: Dual Wingbeat
moves.desc: Hits twice. If the first hit breaks the target's substitute, it will take damage for the second hit.
moves.shortDesc: Hits 2 times in one turn.

moves.name: Steel Wing
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to raise the user's Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to raise the user's Defense by 1.

moves.name: Power Trip
moves.desc: Power is equal to 20+(X*20), where X is the user's total stat stage changes that are greater than 0.
moves.shortDesc: + 20 power for each of the user's stat boosts.

moves.name: Drill Peck
moves.desc: No additional effect.
moves.shortDesc: No additional effect.

moves.name: Light Screen
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the user and its party members take 0.5x damage from special attacks, or 0.66x damage if in a Double Battle. Damage is not reduced further with Aurora Veil. Critical hits ignore this effect. It is removed from the user's side if the user or an ally is successfully hit by Brick Break, Psychic Fangs, or Defog. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Light Clay. Fails if the effect is already active on the user's side.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, special damage to allies is halved.

moves.name: Reflect
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the user and its party members take 0.5x damage from physical attacks, or 0.66x damage if in a Double Battle. Damage is not reduced further with Aurora Veil. Critical hits ignore this effect. It is removed from the user's side if the user or an ally is successfully hit by Brick Break, Psychic Fangs, or Defog. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Light Clay. Fails if the effect is already active on the user's side.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, physical damage to allies is halved.

moves.name: Sunny Day
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the weather becomes Sunny Day. The damage of Fire-type attacks is multiplied by 1.5 and the damage of Water-type attacks is multiplied by 0.5 during the effect. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Heat Rock. Fails if the current weather is Sunny Day.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, intense sunlight powers Fire moves.

moves.name: Agility
moves.desc: Raises the user's Speed by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the user's Speed by 2.

moves.name: Curse
moves.desc: If the user is not a Ghost type, lowers the user's Speed by 1 stage and raises the user's Attack and Defense by 1 stage. If the user is a Ghost type, the user loses 1/2 of its maximum HP, rounded down and even if it would cause fainting, in exchange for the target losing 1/4 of its maximum HP, rounded down, at the end of each turn while it is active. If the target uses Baton Pass, the replacement will continue to be affected. Fails if there is no target or if the target is already affected.
moves.shortDesc: Curses if Ghost, else -1 Spe, +1 Atk, +1 Def.

moves.name: Body Slam
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to paralyze the target. Damage doubles and no accuracy check is done if the target has used Minimize while active.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to paralyze the target.

moves.name: Flash Cannon
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to lower the target's Special Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to lower the target's Sp. Def by 1.

moves.name: Metal Sound
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Special Defense by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's Sp. Def by 2.

moves.name: Rain Dance
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the weather becomes Rain Dance. The damage of Water-type attacks is multiplied by 1.5 and the damage of Fire-type attacks is multiplied by 0.5 during the effect. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Damp Rock. Fails if the current weather is Rain Dance.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, heavy rain powers Water moves.

moves.name: Screech
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Defense by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's Defense by 2.

moves.name: Swagger
moves.desc: Raises the target's Attack by 2 stages and confuses it.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the target's Attack by 2 and confuses it.

moves.name: Fly
moves.desc: This attack charges on the first turn and executes on the second. On the first turn, the user avoids all attacks other than Gust, Hurricane, Sky Uppercut, Smack Down, Thousand Arrows, Thunder, and Twister, and Gust and Twister have doubled power when used against it. If the user is holding a Power Herb, the move completes in one turn.
moves.shortDesc: Flies up on first turn, then strikes the next turn.

moves.name: Substitute
moves.desc: The user takes 1/4 of its maximum HP, rounded down, and puts it into a substitute to take its place in battle. The substitute is removed once enough damage is inflicted on it, or if the user switches out or faints. Baton Pass can be used to transfer the substitute to an ally, and the substitute will keep its remaining HP. Until the substitute is broken, it receives damage from all attacks made by other Pokemon and shields the user from status effects and stat stage changes caused by other Pokemon. Sound-based moves and Pokemon with the Infiltrator Ability ignore substitutes. The user still takes normal damage from weather and status effects while behind its substitute. If the substitute breaks during a multi-hit attack, the user will take damage from any remaining hits. If a substitute is created while the user is trapped by a binding move, the binding effect ends immediately. Fails if the user does not have enough HP remaining to create a substitute without fainting, or if it already has a substitute.
moves.shortDesc: User takes 1/4 its max HP to put in a substitute.

moves.name: Hurricane
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to confuse the target. This move can hit a target using Bounce, Fly, or Sky Drop, or is under the effect of Sky Drop. If the weather is Primordial Sea or Rain Dance, this move does not check accuracy. If the weather is Desolate Land or Sunny Day, this move's accuracy is 50%. If this move is used against a Pokemon holding Utility Umbrella, this move's accuracy remains at 70%.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to confuse target. Can't miss in rain.

moves.name: Nasty Plot
moves.desc: Raises the user's Special Attack by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the user's Sp. Atk by 2.

moves.name: Fake Tears
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Special Defense by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's Sp. Def by 2.

moves.name: Pluck
moves.desc: If this move is successful and the user has not fainted, it steals the target's held Berry if it is holding one and eats it immediately, gaining its effects even if the user's item is being ignored. Items lost to this move cannot be regained with Recycle or the Harvest Ability.
moves.shortDesc: User steals and eats the target's Berry.

moves.name: Sky Attack
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to make the target flinch and a higher chance for a critical hit. This attack charges on the first turn and executes on the second. If the user is holding a Power Herb, the move completes in one turn.
moves.shortDesc: Charges, then hits turn 2. 30% flinch. High crit.

moves.name: Hone Claws
moves.desc: Raises the user's Attack and accuracy by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the user's Attack and accuracy by 1.

moves.name: Spite
moves.desc: Causes the target's last move used to lose 4 PP. Fails if the target has not made a move, if the move has 0 PP, or if it no longer knows the move.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the PP of the target's last move by 4.

moves.name: Air Slash
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to make the target flinch.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to make the target flinch.

moves.name: Double-Edge
moves.desc: If the target lost HP, the user takes recoil damage equal to 33% the HP lost by the target, rounded half up, but not less than 1 HP.
moves.shortDesc: Has 33% recoil.

moves.name: Scary Face
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Speed by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's Speed by 2.

moves.name: Rest
moves.desc: The user falls asleep for the next two turns and restores all of its HP, curing itself of any non-volatile status condition in the process. Fails if the user has full HP, is already asleep, or if another effect is preventing sleep.
moves.shortDesc: User sleeps 2 turns and restores HP and status.

moves.name: Aerial Ace
moves.desc: This move does not check accuracy.
moves.shortDesc: This move does not check accuracy.

moves.name: Leer
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the foe(s) Defense by 1.

moves.name: Steel Beam
moves.desc: Whether or not this move is successful and even if it would cause fainting, the user loses 1/2 of its maximum HP, rounded up, unless the user has the Magic Guard Ability.
moves.shortDesc: User loses 50% max HP.

moves.name: Facade
moves.desc: Power doubles if the user is burned, paralyzed, or poisoned. The physical damage halving effect from the user's burn is ignored.
moves.shortDesc: Power doubles if user is burn/poison/paralyzed.

moves.name: Giga Impact
moves.desc: If this move is successful, the user must recharge on the following turn and cannot select a move.
moves.shortDesc: User cannot move next turn.

moves.name: Metal Claw
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to raise the user's Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to raise the user's Attack by 1.

moves.name: Take Down
moves.desc: If the target lost HP, the user takes recoil damage equal to 1/4 the HP lost by the target, rounded half up, but not less than 1 HP.
moves.shortDesc: Has 1/4 recoil.

moves.name: Rock Smash
moves.desc: Has a 50% chance to lower the target's Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 50% chance to lower the target's Defense by 1.

moves.name: Sleep Talk
moves.desc: One of the user's known moves, besides this move, is selected for use at random. Fails if the user is not asleep. The selected move does not have PP deducted from it, and can currently have 0 PP. This move cannot select Assist, Beak Blast, Belch, Bide, Blazing Torque, Celebrate, Chatter, Combat Torque, Copycat, Dynamax Cannon, Focus Punch, Hold Hands, Magical Torque, Me First, Metronome, Mimic, Mirror Move, Nature Power, Noxious Torque, Shell Trap, Sketch, Sleep Talk, Struggle, Uproar, Wicked Torque, or any two-turn move.
moves.shortDesc: User must be asleep. Uses another known move.

moves.name: Reversal
moves.desc: The power of this move is 20 if X is 33 to 48, 40 if X is 17 to 32, 80 if X is 10 to 16, 100 if X is 5 to 9, 150 if X is 2 to 4, and 200 if X is 0 or 1, where X is equal to (user's current HP * 48 / user's maximum HP), rounded down.
moves.shortDesc: More power the less HP the user has left.

moves.name: Sand Attack
moves.desc: Lowers the target's accuracy by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's accuracy by 1.

abilities.name: Mirror Armor
abilities.desc: When one of this Pokemon's stat stages would be lowered by another Pokemon, that Pokemon's stat stage is lowered instead. This effect does not happen if this Pokemon's stat stage was already -6. If the other Pokemon has a substitute, neither Pokemon has its stat stage lowered.
abilities.shortDesc: If this Pokemon's stat stages would be lowered, the attacker's are lowered instead.

abilities.name: Pressure
abilities.desc: If this Pokemon is the target of an opposing Pokemon's move, that move loses one additional PP. Imprison, Snatch, and Tera Blast also lose one additional PP when used by an opposing Pokemon, but Sticky Web does not.
abilities.shortDesc: If this Pokemon is the target of a foe's move, that move loses one additional PP.

abilities.name: Unnerve
abilities.desc: While this Pokemon is active, it prevents opposing Pokemon from using their Berries. This Ability activates before hazards and other Abilities take effect.
abilities.shortDesc: While this Pokemon is active, it prevents opposing Pokemon from using their Berries.

items.name: Rocky Helmet

items.name: Leftovers
items.desc: At the end of every turn, holder restores 1/16 of its max HP.

items.name: Covert Cloak
items.desc: Holder is not affected by the secondary effect of another Pokemon's attack.

items.name: Safety Goggles
items.desc: Holder is immune to powder moves and damage from Sandstorm or Hail.

items.name: Choice Band

items.name: Sitrus Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/4 max HP when at 1/2 max HP or less. Single use.

items.name: Assault Vest
items.desc: Holder's Sp. Def is 1.5x, but it can only select damaging moves.

items.name: Wiki Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -SpA Nature. Single use.

items.name: Figy Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -Atk Nature. Single use.

items.name: Metronome

items.name: Sky Plate
items.desc: Holder's Flying-type attacks have 1.2x power. Judgment is Flying type.

items.name: Heavy-Duty Boots
items.desc: When switching in, the holder is unaffected by hazards on its side of the field.

items.name: Jaboca Berry
items.desc: If holder is hit by a physical move, attacker loses 1/8 of its max HP. Single use.

items.name: Adrenaline Orb
items.desc: Raises holder's Speed by 1 stage if it gets affected by Intimidate. Single use.

items.name: Mirror Herb
items.desc: When an opposing Pokemon raises a stat stage, the holder copies it. Single use.

items.name: Iapapa Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -Def Nature. Single use.

items.name: Choice Specs
items.desc: Holder's Sp. Atk is 1.5x, but it can only select the first move it executes.

items.name: Wacan Berry
items.desc: Halves damage taken from a supereffective Electric-type attack. Single use.

items.name: Quick Claw
items.desc: Each turn, holder has a 20% chance to move first in its priority bracket.

items.name: Iron Plate
items.desc: Holder's Steel-type attacks have 1.2x power. Judgment is Steel type.

items.name: Mental Herb
items.desc: Cures holder of Attract, Disable, Encore, Heal Block, Taunt, Torment. Single use.

items.name: Eviolite
items.desc: If holder's species can evolve, its Defense and Sp. Def are 1.5x.

items.name: Power Herb
items.desc: Holder's two-turn moves complete in one turn (except Sky Drop). Single use.

items.name: Wide Lens
items.desc: The accuracy of attacks by the holder is 1.1x.

items.name: Chesto Berry
items.desc: Holder wakes up if it is asleep. Single use.

items.name: Focus Sash

items.name: Ability Shield
items.desc: Holder's Ability cannot be changed by any effect.

items.name: Shell Bell
items.desc: After an attack, holder gains 1/8 of the damage in HP dealt to other Pokemon.

items.name: Air Balloon
items.desc: Holder is immune to Ground-type attacks. Pops when holder is hit.

items.name: Weakness Policy
items.desc: If holder is hit super effectively, raises Attack, Sp. Atk by 2 stages. Single use.

items.name: Metal Coat
items.desc: Holder's Steel-type attacks have 1.2x power. Evolves Onix into Steelix and Scyther into Scizor when traded.

items.name: Psychic Seed
items.desc: If the terrain is Psychic Terrain, raises holder's Sp. Def by 1 stage. Single use.

items.name: Black Sludge
items.desc: Each turn, if holder is a Poison type, restores 1/16 max HP; loses 1/8 if not.

items.name: Electric Seed
items.desc: If the terrain is Electric Terrain, raises holder's Defense by 1 stage. Single use.

items.name: Protective Pads
items.desc: Holder's moves are protected from adverse contact effects, except Pickpocket.

items.name: Utility Umbrella
items.desc: The holder ignores rain- and sun-based effects. Damage and accuracy calculations from attacks used by the holder are affected by rain and sun, but not attacks used against the holder.

items.name: Damp Rock
items.desc: Holder's use of Rain Dance lasts 8 turns instead of 5.

items.name: Misty Seed
items.desc: If the terrain is Misty Terrain, raises holder's Sp. Def by 1 stage. Single use.

items.name: Focus Band
items.desc: Holder has a 10% chance to survive an attack that would KO it with 1 HP.

items.name: Clear Amulet
items.desc: Prevents other Pokemon from lowering the holder's stat stages.

items.name: Kee Berry
items.desc: Raises holder's Defense by 1 stage after it is hit by a physical attack. Single use.

items.name: Zoom Lens
items.desc: The accuracy of attacks by the holder is 1.2x if it moves after its target.

items.name: Eject Button
items.desc: If holder survives a hit, it immediately switches out to a chosen ally. Single use.

items.name: Bright Powder
items.desc: The accuracy of attacks against the holder is 0.9x.

items.name: Custap Berry
items.desc: Holder moves first in its priority bracket when at 1/4 max HP or less. Single use.
